  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recent studies indicated the central venous pressure (CVP) as a prognostic marker. Therefore,
      we retrospectively analyzed the CVP on admission to the intensive care unit (ICU) in cardiac
      surgery patients regarding its prognostic value for morbidity and mortality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
